                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3418: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-05T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 5, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. Department’s telegram December 4, 5 p.m.<note n="46" xml:id="d340fn46">See
                        footnote 45, <ref target="#pg_369">p. 369</ref>.</note> complied with. I
                    propose in future to repeat to the American Delegation at Montevideo and the
                    Legation at La Paz for its confidential information telegrams to the Department
                    concerning Paraguayan-Bolivian relations, send them copies of pertinent
                    despatches, the latter to be forwarded through the Embassy at Buenos Aires.
                    Please telegraph approval and instruct Legation at La Paz to reciprocate.<note
                        n="47" xml:id="d340fn47">Telegram No. 111 was approved in telegraphic
                        instruction No. 31, December 7, 6 p.m.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
